data.value: -Is completely enclosed in Blocks (aside from the entrance) to serve as side walls, a floor, and a ceiling. You may also use Wood Platforms as part of the -Has background Walls. Walls not placed by a player (such as naturally-occurring dirt) do not count, with the exception of those behind Floating Island structures or the Planked Walls found in naturally occurring structures in caverns. -Has at least 1 placed Comfort item. (Chairs & tables, beds, etc) -Has at least 1 placed Flat Surface item. (Tables) -Has at least 1 entrance, which can be a Wooden Door in a wall or a Wood Platform in the ceiling or floor. -Has at least 1 light source. A Furnace, Lamp Post, or Disco Ball will not work for this purpose. -Is at least 5 blocks tall and 10 blocks wide (or 4 blocks tall and 8 blocks wide, not including walls, floor or ceiling)An easy way to check this is to put a bed in the room where you want the NPC to move in and try to set your spawn with it, if you can set it then the room is inhabitable. This is obsolete since the 1.1 patch where you can use the housing query instead
